      "para_id": "Q001569.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝišzida , his personal god , Ur-Ninĝirsu , ruler of Lagaš , son of Gudea , ruler of Lagaš , the builder Ninĝirsu's E-ninnu , fashioned his own statue . He named this statue for his sake “As I am someone loved by his personal god , may my life be prolonged!” , and brought it before him into his temple ."
    }
  ],
